# LifeLink — Forensic-Level Technical Analysis

> **Analyst Posture:** CTO · Senior Full-Stack Engineer · University Examiner · Security Auditor · Product Strategist
> **Codebase Stats:** ~10,278 LOC · 50+ source files · Node.js / Express 5 / MongoDB (Mongoose 9)
> **Date:** 2026-04-26

---

# EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

LifeLink is a **backend API for a blood & organ donation coordination platform** connecting donors, hospitals, and administrators. It is designed as the server for a **Flutter mobile application**.

**Honest verdict:** This is an **above-average graduation project** with genuinely impressive depth in certain areas (gamification engine, admin analytics, auth flows) but has critical gaps that would prevent production deployment (no unit tests, exposed credentials, incomplete geo-matching). The architecture is clean and follows professional patterns — far beyond what most graduation projects achieve.

**Overall Score: 74/100** — Strong B+. With 30 days of focused work, this could reach A/A+ territory.

---

# PROJECT DNA

| Dimension | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Problem** | Connects blood/organ donors with hospitals; gamifies donations to increase engagement |
| **Users** | Donors (individuals), Hospitals (institutions), Admins (platform operators) |
| **Business Model** | Social-impact platform; potential B2G (government health ministry) or B2B (hospital SaaS) |
| **Maturity** | Late Alpha — core flows implemented, not production-hardened |
| **Architecture** | Layered MVC+S (Routes → Controllers → Services → Models) |
| **Module System** | ES Modules (`"type": "module"`) |
| **Runtime** | Node.js with Express 5.2.1 (cutting-edge) |
| **Database** | MongoDB Atlas (Mongoose 9.1.6 ODM) |
| **Auth** | JWT (access + refresh tokens), bcrypt, 2FA (TOTP), OTP password reset |
| **Notifications** | Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) + in-app notification system |
| **Email** | Nodemailer with SMTP + HTML templates |
| **API Docs** | OpenAPI 3.0 via Swagger UI + YAML source of truth |
| **Frontend** | Flutter (separate repo — this is backend only) |

