# FULL TECHNICAL BREAKDOWN

## Folder Structure

```
LifeLink/
├── src/
│   ├── app.js              # Express app configuration, middleware chain, route mounting
│   ├── server.js           # DB connect, seed, listen, graceful shutdown
│   ├── config/
│   │   ├── db.js           # MongoDB connection with pool config
│   │   ├── env.js          # Centralized env parsing + validation
│   │   └── swagger.js      # OpenAPI spec generation
│   ├── controllers/        # 8 controllers — HTTP layer (req/res handling)
│   ├── services/           # 7 services — Business logic layer
│   ├── models/             # 21 Mongoose models
│   ├── middlewares/         # 5 middlewares (auth, role, error, rate-limit, maintenance)
│   ├── routes/             # 9 route files with Swagger JSDoc annotations
│   ├── utils/              # 8 utility modules (JWT, mailer, FCM, geo, pagination, etc.)
│   └── validation/         # 2 validation modules (auth, admin)
├── scripts/                # 7 scripts (seed, smoke test, E2E auth, OpenAPI gen)
├── docs/                   # API docs, Postman collection, release notes
├── public/                 # Static files (Swagger docs hosting)
├── openapi.yaml            # OpenAPI source of truth (20KB)
└── openapi.json            # Generated OpenAPI spec (82KB)
```

**Architecture Style:** Clean **Layered Architecture** with proper separation of concerns:
- **Routes** → Define endpoints + Swagger annotations
- **Controllers** → Parse HTTP input, call services, format HTTP output
- **Services** → Pure business logic, database operations
- **Models** → Data schema + validation + hooks

**Coding Conventions:**
- Consistent ES Module imports
- Named exports for services, default exports for models
- camelCase variables, PascalCase models
- JSDoc comments on most public functions
- Consistent error message patterns

