# DATABASE REVIEW

## Schema Design (21 Models)

| Model | Purpose | Design Quality |
|---|---|---|
| **User** | Base schema with discriminators | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Excellent use of Mongoose discriminators |
| **Donor** | Extends User (blood type, DOB, availability) | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Good |
| **Hospital** | Extends User (license, hospitalId) | ⭐⭐⭐ Adequate |
| **Request** | Blood/organ donation requests | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Well-indexed, thorough validation |
| **Donation** | Tracks donation lifecycle | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Good with compound indexes |
| **Notification** | In-app notification system | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Well-structured with aggregation support |
| **DonorPoints** | Points balance + tier tracking | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Excellent atomic design |
| **PointsTransaction** | Immutable points audit log | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Dedup via partial unique index |
| **Badge / UserBadge** | Achievement system | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Clean normalized design |
| **RewardCatalog / RewardRedemption** | Reward system | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Production-ready with limits |
| **OneTimeOtp** | Password reset OTPs | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ TTL auto-cleanup |
| **TwoFactor** | 2FA secrets + backup codes | ⭐⭐⭐ Functional |
| **RefreshTokenBlacklist** | Token revocation | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ TTL-based auto-purge |
| **AuditLog** | Admin action trail | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ Immutable, indexed |
| **SystemSettings** | Key-value config store | ⭐⭐⭐ Simple but effective |

### Indexes — **Impressively thorough** (40+ indexes)
- Compound indexes on high-frequency query patterns (`donorId + status`, `userId + read`)
- 2dsphere index on user coordinates (future geo queries)
- TTL indexes for auto-cleanup (OTP, blacklisted tokens)
- Partial unique index for deduplication (points transactions)

### Weak Points
1. **No Mongoose transactions on donation creation** — Race condition possible when two donors respond simultaneously
2. **Hospital `ref: 'Hospital'`** in Request model should be `ref: 'User'` (discriminator models share the User collection)
3. **2FA secrets stored in plaintext** — Should be encrypted at rest
4. **No data archival strategy** — Notifications and transactions will grow unbounded

