# CODE QUALITY REVIEW

| Metric | Score | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Clean Code** | 7/10 | Consistent patterns, some dead code |
| **Naming** | 8/10 | Descriptive, follows JS conventions |
| **Separation of Concerns** | 9/10 | Clean Controller→Service→Model layers |
| **Maintainability** | 7/10 | Good structure, lacks tests |
| **Reusability** | 7/10 | Utilities are well-extracted |
| **Readability** | 8/10 | Good comments, clear flow |
| **Technical Debt** | 6/10 | Placeholder geo-scoring, Windows-specific code |

### Anti-Patterns Detected
1. **Catch-and-rethrow** — Several services catch errors only to throw them again
2. **String-based error matching** in controllers (`if (error.message === 'exact string')`) — fragile
3. **Duplicate validation** — Donor model validates blood type AND controller validates it again
4. **Inconsistent pagination** — Some endpoints use `skip/limit`, others `page/limit`, the utility supports both but it's confusing

